00:19:11.520 --> 00:19:13.760
which is interesting I think.

00:19:13.760 --> 00:19:15.920
The Rilke poetry that he go into,

00:19:15.920 --> 00:19:19.200
different from the expressionist
folks like [inaudible]

00:19:19.200 --> 00:19:24.600 position:56%
in that it was seeking to go more
after this new objectivity movement,

00:19:24.600 --> 00:19:26.020
rather than the expressionist
movement.

00:19:26.020 --> 00:19:28.740
So, we have this juxtaposition
of let's look inward,

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:32.240
let's tell our personal experience,
or let's convey the experience

00:19:32.240 --> 00:19:37.880
of a figure in the text, to this
quote and quote, objective music

00:19:37.880 --> 00:19:41.130
that seems to ignore what's
actually going on in society.

00:19:41.130 --> 00:19:45.010
And maybe, he's making a
commentary that some parts

00:19:45.010 --> 00:19:48.260
of society ignore what's
actually going on, regardless --

00:19:48.260 --> 00:19:50.320
maybe because their
position in society.

00:19:50.320 --> 00:19:52.970
And then, others being much
more directly affected.

00:19:59.730 --> 00:20:03.480
One of the great quotes from the
phrasure by [inaudible] from music

00:20:03.480 --> 00:20:06.850
and letters, was that
Hindemith sought to bring art

00:20:06.850 --> 00:20:10.790
down to the level of life and to
raise life to the level of art.

00:20:10.790 --> 00:20:12.910
So, there's this constant struggle

00:20:12.910 --> 00:20:17.220
between where the music is being
positioned, in terms of relevance

00:20:17.220 --> 00:20:22.600
for himself, and also
for his audiences.

00:20:22.600 --> 00:20:25.110
The specific works that
we're going to get into,

00:20:25.110 --> 00:20:29.930
from the expressionist
period, represent response

00:20:29.930 --> 00:20:34.770
to what encyclopedia
pretend to call the chaos

00:20:34.770 --> 00:20:36.970
and suffering of modern life.

00:20:36.970 --> 00:20:41.040
There's a lot of references to
colors, and the texts, which may

00:20:41.040 --> 00:20:43.750
